reviews.review_text: East coast dead I love the 80's shows, and form me Hampton was always a winner. Like a big space ship....you know.

How did this one slip by? Quite a gem for a season of Dead shows I normally overlook (Rhode Island show later that month was also great). 

Short but sweet. Stranger, Terrapin, and Dew are major highlights worth grabbing this "on" show for. 

Thanks CM

Fat chick polka? Great show.  Best source as of today.  Starting with 3/31/84 the entire run through the E. Coast is chock full of spacey goodness and nearly all these shows are worthy of an attentive listen.  

"A polka for big fat chicks" - MIckey Hart before CC Rider.
Solid 84 Show Highlights: Let It Grow
